# Styling Guidelines

## CSS Modules
- Use CSS modules (`.module.scss`) for component-specific styles
- Import styles as `import styles from './index.module.scss'`
- Use `className={styles.className}` for applying styles
- Avoid global CSS classes in component modules

## Global Styles
- Global styles should go in [src/main.scss](mdc:src/main.scss)
- App-level styles should go in [src/App.scss](mdc:src/App.scss)
- Use global styles sparingly, prefer CSS modules

## SCSS Features
- Use SCSS variables and mixins for consistency
- Leverage nesting appropriately (max 3 levels deep)
- Use BEM methodology for class naming in modules
- Organize styles logically within files

## Responsive Design
- Use mobile-first approach for responsive design
- Test on various screen sizes
- Use relative units (rem, em, %) where appropriate
- Consider touch targets for mobile devices

## Image Assets
- Image assets are located in [src/assets/img/](mdc:src/assets/img/)
- Use appropriate image formats (WebP, PNG, SVG)
- Consider image optimization for performance
- Use CSS for simple graphics when possible

## Style Organization
- Keep styles close to their components
- Use consistent naming conventions
- Group related styles together
- Comment complex styling logic
